race.description: Celebrate 2025 At Callaghan Park Maiden Handicap
race.comment: SENZORA (6) debuts and beat four others by 25L here in a recent trial. Butler sticks aboard from that and count on him to manage the awkward gate. Shows promise, and it's hard to risk the super-striking Taylor stable. Stablemate BITTER SPIRIT (1) found a place but was disappointing here first up after being fractious at the barriers. He showed plenty in his maiden preparation, and Huxtable takes over today. Some trust is required, but he brings the best figures. TIME POWER (7) peaks off two threatening efforts at Mackay. He drops back to a shorter sprint but is going well enough to feature. AUGUST JOE (3) raced handy on debut but had to be content with a second placing behind a dominant winner. Draws low again and has a 3kg claimer aboard today. Strips fitter and deserves consideration.
